txt.en: 'But surely this is not so unwholesome as Bilbo's descriptions of Mirkwood.'
'I only hope my legs obey. I really cannot catch my breath in this place!'
'The sun must peep in sometimes!'
'This place does not feel black or evil. It's just...'
'...TREE-ish. Frightfully so.'
'This is a stuffy old place, isn't it, Pippin? I want some air!'
Little Creature
Little Creature
'I wouldn't mind finding some fresh water or a hot meal, either, after that ordeal with the Orcs!'
'The air really is unnaturally dim and dense in here....'
'But I don't think stopping here will get us any of it.'
'It brings to mind a room in my family's Great Hall, the Smials in Tuckborough.'
'Come, Merry! Up you go.'
'Nothing in that room has stirred for generations.'
'There we go....'
'It was unchanged while the Old Took grew old and shabby in there, and unchanged since he died....'
'If the maps in Rivendell speak true, we may find a river this way, towards the south-west.'
'...But that musty room is nothing next to the strange, old air of this wood.'
'Just look at all those trailing, sagging beards of lichen!'
'Splendid! Try not to get us too lost, Master Brandybuck.'
